==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tenuous
<hw>Ten"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tenuis</ets> thin. See <er>Thin</er>, and cf.
<er>Tenuis</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Thin; slender; small;
minute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rare; subtile; not dense; -- said of
fluids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 3. Fig. <def>Lacking substance, as a tenuous argument.</def>
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenure</ent>⟦br⟧
